# Headroom Proxy Provider Configuration
# Copy this file to ~/.config/headroom/proxy.env and uncomment ONE provider block.
# Then run: systemctl --user restart headroom-proxy
#
# The proxy supports ONE backend at a time. To use multiple providers simultaneously,
# run additional proxy instances on different ports (see README.md).

# =============================================================================
# PROVIDER: OpenAI API (default)
# =============================================================================
# No extra configuration needed. The proxy forwards OpenAI-compatible requests
# to https://api.openai.com by default.
# OPENAI_TARGET_API_URL=https://api.openai.com

# =============================================================================
# PROVIDER: Anthropic API
# =============================================================================
# Anthropic uses a separate endpoint (/v1/messages). Set your API key:
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# =============================================================================
# PROVIDER: OpenRouter (400+ models)
# =============================================================================
# Uncomment to route all OpenAI-compatible traffic through OpenRouter.
# Set your OpenRouter API key in your shell or in this file.
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...
# OPENAI_TARGET_API_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1

# =============================================================================
# PROVIDER: OpenCode Zen
# =============================================================================
# OpenCode Zen is a unified AI gateway. Uncomment the endpoint for your model format.
# Get your API key from https://opencode.ai/zen
#
# For OpenAI-compatible models (GPT, Qwen, DeepSeek, etc.):
# OPENAI_TARGET_API_URL=https://opencode.ai/zen/v1/chat/completions
#
# For Anthropic-compatible models (Claude):
# ANTHROPIC_TARGET_API_URL=https://opencode.ai/zen/v1/messages
#
# For Google Gemini models:
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=...
# OPENAI_TARGET_API_URL=https://opencode.ai/zen/v1/models/gemini-3.1-pro

# =============================================================================
# PROVIDER: Google Gemini / Vertex AI
# =============================================================================
# For Google Cloud Vertex AI (requires GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS):
# Use --backend vertex_ai (configured via proxy command override in service file)
#
# For Google AI Studio (generativeai.googleapis.com):
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=...
# OPENAI_TARGET_API_URL=https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta

# =============================================================================
# PROVIDER: GitHub Copilot
# =============================================================================
# Copilot requires special auth. Use `headroom wrap copilot` instead of the proxy.
# See: headroom wrap copilot -- --model gpt-4o
# Or configure Copilot CLI directly:
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghu_...

# =============================================================================
# ADVANCED: Multi-provider setup
# =============================================================================
# To use multiple providers at once, run additional proxy instances:
#
#   headroom proxy --port 8788 --backend openrouter
#   headroom proxy --port 8789 --openai-api-url https://opencode.ai/zen/v1
#
# Then point different tools at different ports:
#
#   OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8788/v1 opencode
#   OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8789/v1 hermes chat
